node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Glacier_National_Park 🦋 in Glacier National Park with @missjessbess, and @glaciernps. May be an image of flower, tree and nature.

node.text:
Photo by @missjessbess 
•
There’s something about flowers, and more specifically wildflowers that draw us in.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I’ve photographed flowers all over the states from deserts to mountains. It’s inspiring to see these little beauties thriving in the unlikely or even harsh environments.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Now don’t get me wrong sometimes wildflowers can be a down right pain to capture. The slightest breeze can have you waiting forever for a break in the wind to catch just a single still shot. 
•
#goingtothesunroad☀️ 
Leave No Trace • Don’t pick the wildflowers 💐

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Glacier_National_Park 🦋 in Glacier National Park with @glaciernps, and @_jeffreyji. May be an image of lake and nature.

node.text:
Photo by @_jeffreyji
•
“Gem in the Mountains”
#grinnellglacier 
.
Diving back into the archives!
•
People often ask me, what my favorite national park in the US is. My answer has been Glacier for a number of years now. Why? Well, I think this image says it all. Apart from having one of my favorite scenic roads in the US, Glacier also has hikes that boast views such as this.
.
Wild flowers, mountains, lakes, forests, waterfalls, and glaciers, this national park has it all. Of course, it has one of the most scenic roads that is awe evoking. But I always say, to really get to know a national park, you have to hike it. And there’s a reason Glacier is known as the hiker’s national park. Spend a day hiking here and you’re greeted with sprawling scenes that are vibrant, colorful, and dramatic. It truly feels like a hiker’s paradise!
